        <ol class="fs-5">
          <li>
            <strong>Practice Deep Breathing:</strong> Slow, deep breaths can help calm your nervous system.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Meditate:</strong> Use mindfulness or meditation techniques to center your thoughts.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Use Ayurvedic Herbs:</strong> Consider natural remedies like ashwagandha or brahmi to ease stress.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Take a Gentle Walk:</strong> Light physical activity can help release tension.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Ground Yourself:</strong> Use grounding techniques such as focusing on your surroundings.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">What Not To Do:</h3>
        <ul class="fs-5">
          <li>Do not try to suppress your emotions forcefully.</li>
          <li>Avoid caffeine and other stimulants that may worsen anxiety.</li>
          <li>Refrain from self-medicating without professional guidance.</li>
